' Usage Flow
note as UsageNote
  **Usage (Identical Everywhere)**
  
  ```typescript
  // In Node.js
  import { ONCE } from './layer1/ONCE.js';
  const kernel = await ONCE.start(scenario);
  
  // In Browser
  import { ONCE } from '/ONCE/0.3.21.6/layer1/ONCE.js';
  const kernel = await ONCE.start(scenario);
  
  // In Worker
  import { ONCE } from '../layer1/ONCE.js';
  const kernel = await ONCE.start(scenario);
  
  // Always returns ONCEKernel interface
  const health = await kernel.getHealth();
  const result = await kernel.invokeMethod('getPeers', {});
  ```
end note

' Environment Detection Flow
note as DetectionFlow
  **Environment Detection Logic**
  
  1. Check typeof window
     → if undefined: Node.js or Worker
  2. Check typeof self
     → if ServiceWorkerGlobalScope: Service Worker
     → if DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope: Web Worker
  3. Check window.navigator.standalone
     → if true: PWA
     → else: Browser
  4. Check process.versions?.node
     → if exists: Node.js
  
  Return appropriate kernel:
  - Node.js → DefaultONCE
  - Browser → BrowserONCEKernel
  - Worker → WorkerONCEKernel
  - ServiceWorker → ServiceWorkerONCEKernel
end note

UsageNote .. ONCE
DetectionFlow .. ONCE

' P2P Network
package "P2P Network" as Network <<Cloud>> {
  node "Node Peer" as NodePeer {
    component "DefaultONCE" as Node1
  }
  
  node "Browser Peer" as BrowserPeer {
    component "BrowserONCEKernel" as Browser1
  }
  
  node "Worker Peer" as WorkerPeer {
    component "WorkerONCEKernel" as Worker1
  }
  
  node "ServiceWorker Peer" as SWPeer {
    component "ServiceWorkerONCEKernel" as SW1
  }
}

Node1 <--> Browser1 : scenario\nstate transfer
Browser1 <--> Worker1 : P2P\ncommunication
Worker1 <--> SW1 : mesh\nnetwork
SW1 <--> Node1 : peer\ndiscovery

note bottom of Network
  **All peers are equal**
  No client/server distinction
  Just ONCE kernels communicating
  via scenario state transfer
end note

